41. How can you use regular expressions to extract all email addresses from a given string using an array in
PHP?
<?php
// Input string with multiple email addresses
$text = "Contact us at admin@example.com, support@mail.com or sales123@company.org for more info.";

// Regular expression pattern for emails
$pattern = "/[a-zA-Z0-9._%+-]+@[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,}/";

// Extract all emails into an array
preg_match_all($pattern, $text, $matches);

// $matches[0] contains all the found emails
$emails = $matches[0];

// Display results
echo "Extracted Email Addresses:<br>";
print_r($emails);
?>
